author: Erica_Frenkel;
title: The universal anesthesia machine

aws-transcripts.transcript: I'm gonna talk to you today about the design of medical technology for low resource setting. I study health systems in these countries, and one of the major gaps in care almost across the board is access to safe surgery. Now, one of the major bottlenecks that we've found that sort of preventing both the access on the first place and the safety of those surgeries that do happen is anesthesia. And actually, it's the model that we expect toe work for delivering anesthesia in these environments. Here we have a scene that you'd find in any operating room across the U. S. Or any other developed country in the background. There is a very sophisticated anesthesia machine, and this machine is able to enable surgery and save lives because it was designed with this environment in mind in order to operate, this machine needs a number of things that this hospital has to offer. It needs an extremely well trained ah anesthesiologist with years of training with complex machines to help her monitor the flows off the gas and keep her patients safe and anesthetized throughout the surgery.
